'''Martha Richler''' is an art historian and cartoonist.  Working for the ''[[London Evening Standard|Evening Standard]]'', she was the first woman to produce a daily cartoon for the newspapers based in London, known collectively as "[[Fleet_Street#Printing_and_journalism|Fleet Street]]".  Her father is the writer [[Mordecai Richler]] and her pen name, '''Marf''', is his name for her.  She produces work for web sites, including [[PoliticalBetting.com]].<ref name=BCA/>

